      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and failure load are the primary regulatory quantities of interest for Class II spinal fixation devices under ASTM F1717; peak pedicle-screw stress is a secondary QoI directly linked to clinical fatigue risk."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities replicate the intended regulatory submission context (ASTM F1717 static compression-bending, non-cannulated 7.5 mm screw, Class II device); geometry, loading mode, and material system are identical to the intended-use configuration described in the claim and requirement nodes."
    }
